                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-27T21:00:00-06:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Demand delivered at six o’clock this evening and General Quintana replied that he
                    has already reported the arrest of Cantú to General Téllez, Chief of Division at
                    Monterey, who is his superior officer, and is unable to accede to demands
                    without orders from him. There is no doubt about Cantu being enticed to middle
                    of bridge and kidnapped on American side of boundary and forced to cross
                    boundary. Department should press demand through Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
